<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1119,1482]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,322,1231,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Remarks:</emphasis>
Due to the similar the integument sculpture (formed exclusively by fine denticles) and P- 
<number box="[1423,1436,1232,1258]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="3.0">3</number>
bearing one ventral seta (
<figureCitation box="[444,533,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 6 A – C" captionStartId="9.[151,255,1662,1686]" captionTargetBox="[201,1388,564,1617]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[169,1418,530,1641]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6 A – C. Sperchon ayyildizi sp. nov., female: A = idiosoma, ventral view, B = capitulum, C = palp, lateral view. Scale bars = 100 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196108/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number box="[498,513,1269,1295]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="6.0">6</number>
C
</figureCitation>
–D), 
<taxonomicName box="[592,869,1269,1294]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarnogradskii">
<emphasis box="[592,869,1269,1294]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">Sperchon tarnogradskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<emphasis box="[1089,1209,1269,1294]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">S. insignis</emphasis>
Walter, 
<number box="[1306,1367,1269,1295]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="1906.0">1906</number>
, from which it differs exclusively in P- 
<number box="[556,569,1306,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="3.0">3</number>
being larger in size. The variability of further populations needs to be examined to clarify the taxonomy. 
<figureCitation box="[574,743,1344,1370]" captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – E" captionStartId="7.[151,256,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[204,1407,977,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,964,1964]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – E. Sperchon tarnogradskii (A – C = male, D – E = female): A = idiosoma, ventral view; B = palp, lateral view; C = palp, medial view; D = palp, medial view; E = chelicera. Scale bars = 100 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196106/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="41">
Figures 
<number box="[673,687,1344,1370]" pageId="6" pageNumber="41" value="4.0">4</number>
A–E
</figureCitation>
show some morphological details of the specimens from Bingöl Province.
</paragraph>
